<---------------------------------Explaination---------------------------------------->

1. Process vs Object Oriented :
-> process ko hamm procedural bhi bolte hai isme hamar pura data ek function ke andar hota
hai matlab ki hamara pura data function ke andar hi ghumega.
-> for example :- ham ek banking system bana rhae hai to procesdural me important hai
ki kaam kya kya karna hai matlab sirf withdraw , deposit and transfer bass procedural
me itna hi socha jayega procedural me ham direct kaam soach te hai ki hamko kya kya
karna hoga uss hisab se ham apna function lhikte hai.
-> object oriented me hamara pura data objects ke andar rheta hai and hamar pura data
classes ya to object ke ass pass ghumta hai.
-> for example :- ham ek banking system bana rhae hai to object oriented hame ye soche
nge phele ki isme objects kya kya hai and whai objects ke related hamara data hoga
banking system me hamare objects honge customer , money , account.
customer:- ye paisa deposite , withdraw , transfer karshakta hai etc.
money :- isme ham ye lhik shakte hai ki paisa kitne baje depsoite hua ya to kitne baje
paisa nikla pura paise ka hisab rhakega ye object.
account :- isme ham ye lhik shakte hai ki hamara account kab create hu account ka malik
kon hai account ke kitna transaction hua and bhot kuch.
-> iske andar ham apne data ka bheaviour bhi change kar shakte hai.
-> hame problem milte to shabse phele soach na hai ki isme objects konse konse hai
ya actor kon kon hai problem question me.

2. Instance Variables and Methods
-> shamjo sirf jo bhi niche lhika raha hu

class Cat
properties :- four legs , mustache,fluffy , tail , teeth , do kan.
methods :- lie , mew , jump , scratch.
-> ye jo properties hai isiko ham bolte hai instance variables
and methods bolte hai instance methods

class Car
attributes :- fuel , maxspeed.
methods :- refule() , getfuel() , setSpeed() , getSpeed().
-> attributes ko ham properties bhi bolte hai.

3. Declaring and Using Objects
-> Car myCar = new Car();
-> ye uppar hamne banya hai ek object phela wala jo Car hai wo hamara class name hai .
-> myCar hamara refrence hai jisko ham variable bolte the.
-> new ki madat se ham ek object bana pa rahe hai and object ka name hai Car() and
iska ham addres dal denge myCar ke andar .
-> jab ham koi naya object banate hai to uske shat ek address bhi create hojata hai
jisko haam refrence ke andar pass karte hai .
-> jab bhi hamko mycar() ka object chaiye hoga to ham myCar se lelenge simple.
-> heap ke andar hamare object ki memory allocate hai .
-> Car() isko ham constructor bh bolte hai.
-> me iske behaviour ko acces kar shakta hu . se myCar.addFuel();

4. Class vs Object
-> class ka matlab hota hai sirf blueprint wo accutal me koi memory nhai leta class
hame sirf ye bata hai ki to tum uski madat se kya bana shakte ho or kaise bana shakte ho .
-> object ki maddat se ham wo cizz actual me banate hai.
-> heap ke andar ham apni object ki memory ko allocate karte hai.

5. This & Static Keyword
->this ka matlab hota hai apna current object.
-> static wale method ke andar hame direct instance variable ko nhai lhik shakte hai
hame object ke shaat hi lhik na hoga.
-> static hamesa class ke je ass pass rheta hai .
-> static se jo bhi ham method bana te hai usko hame direct class ke shaat call karna hoga
or jha ham call kar rhae honge wo method bhi static hona chaiye.
-> main method me jo static hota hai wo isliye hota hai ki JVM ko object bana na nhai chhata
-> agar hame static ko use karna hai to direct class.static() aise call karna hoga

6. Constructors & Code Blocks
-> Constructor ko hi ham builder bolte hai class or blueprint ki basis par object create
karta hai compiler apni class me automatic constructor daldeta by default .
-> Constructor ye metod jaisa hi hota hai par ye kuch return nhai karta kyuki
ye ek khud hi wo object return karta hai.
-> Constructor ka name whai hoga jo apni class ka name hoga
-> Constructor me ham by default value pass karte hai jo jab hamara new keyword object
banya jayega to apna Constructor automatic apni instance variabel ki bydefalut value
set kardega ham chae to use change bhi kar shakte hai through our object.
-> Constructor me ok bhi ham parameter pass karte hai to naya object banate shamye hamko wo parameter me
value dena padega nhai to hamra naya object nhai banega .
-> intialization wala code block shabse phele call hota hai Constructor se bhi pheles.
-> code block har object create hone pe call hoga.
-> static block sirf ek barr call hoga wo bhi jab apni class load hogi.

7. Stack vs Heap Memory
-> Memory hamare pass sirf do taraha ki hoti hai stack ya to heap memory.
-> stack ka matlab hai ek ke upar ek stack me ham sirf uppar se phela hi nikal shakte hai data ye to
variables.
-> for example :- ham shadi me gaye wha pe thali kaise rhaki hoti hai ek ke upar ek and hamko
shabse pheli wali hi uhtana hota hai.
-> stack me hamare sare primitive data types and methods store hote hai and whai se excution
hota hai shabse phele jo hoga upar se wo phele chalega .
-> for example:- main() iske andar ek or method hai driver() name ka driver me hamne println ko call
kiya hai to shabse phele memory me kya 1)main() 2) driver() 3) println() => to ye shab ye order me
execute hoga shabse phele chalega main method and so on jo hamne variable define kiya hai method
ke andar wo shab bhi excution ke time pe exceute hojayega and execution ke bad nikal jayega.
-> execution wale part ko bolenge ham callstack.
-> Heap ko hindi me bolte hai dherr matalb bhikra hua koi order nhai hai iska set hone ka iddhar udhar
pada hua hota hai.
-> Heap me hamara object allocate hota hai.
-> insense jo bhi ham new key word se bana rahe honge wo shab hamra heap memory me store hora hai.
-> jab ham object banate hai to hamare pass do chiz hoti hai reference and object refernce stack me
store hoga and object heap me.
-> ye shab stack and heap shab kuch dyanamicaly hota hai.
->REFRENCE BY DEFAULT EK INTEGER HOTA HAI.

8. Primitive vs Reference Types
->java notes jake dhek whai shamj ayega kyu ki isme lhikne layak kuch nhai hai.

9. Variable Scopes
-> ye to aata hi hai revise ke liye java notes jake dhek.

10.Garbage Collection & Finalize
-> Garbage ka matlab hai aisa object jo koi use nhai kar shakta or nhai karne wala hai to usse khete
hai garbage and garbage milke bana dete ek collection to isse bolte hai garbage collection
-> ye jo bhi fhaltu ke objects hote hai joki koi use nhai kar shakta or use karne wala bhi nhai
to uski memory jitni allocate hui thi wo us memory ko wapis khali kardega khali karne or bolte
hai deallocation memory wapis leli jvm ne.
-> jvm kasie pakdega garbage object ko object ke references aise object joki stack me refrence na kar
raha ho ya to koi point nhai ban raha ho
-> object ka koi refrence nhai hai ya to wo unreachable hai to wo garbage collection unhe pakad ke uddhar
hi pel dega or memory khali kardega
-> isme genrations bhi hoti hai jaise ki young , old , permanent generation,
-> JVM har 2 ya 3 min me ek heap ma chhakar marta and dhekta hai kiska reference nhai hai
ya konsa object use nhai hora usko uhta ke bharr fhek dega and memory deallocate kardega .
-> ye puri ek cycle jise ham bolte hai GCC(Garbage Collection Cycle)
-> garbage collection ka matlab hai ki heap andar jao or dheko ki konsi konsi object ka reference
nhai milra stack wale me and kon faltu ka pada hua hai usko bhar uhta ke fhek do and memory
deallocate kardo .
->garbage collection heap memory ko khali karne ka kaam karta hai.